  "prompt": "When entering the US will I be detained for a bench warrant?",
  "response": "Entering the U.S. with an outstanding bench warrant can potentially lead to detention by immigration or law enforcement authorities. A bench warrant typically indicates that a judge has issued an order for your arrest due to failure to comply with court orders, such as appearance in court.\n\nIf you have a bench warrant against you and you are entering the U.S., it's advisable to consult with a legal professional who understands immigration and criminal law. They can provide guidance based on your specific circumstances and help you understand potential consequences and options.",
